    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-5">
            <h2 style="margin-top:70px">Why donate blood?</h2>
            <p>Up to 3 people’s lives can be saved with just 1 donation. 
            There are always people in need of blood. 
            Blood pumped by our heart and running through our veins. 
            It cannot be artificially synthesized or be replaced by another fluid. 
            Start donating blood periodically today, instead of waiting for a time of need and emergency. 
            You ensure adequate blood reserves are available for you and your family 
            (There is a feeling of deep hearted satisfaction having helped people in need).
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-5" style="margin-left:100px;">
            <h2 style="margin-top:70px">Where the Blood Goes?</h2>
            <p>
                You might ask where the blood you donated goes.
                It is first tested and processed before being given to recipients to make sure it is safe for administering.
                For example, Red Cell components in the blood have a life of 35 days,
                while platelets last for only 7 days. This shows it is crucial to have a fresh blood supply at all times,
                made possible through regular blood drives and healthy blood donors.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
  
    <div class="row" style="margin-top:70px">
