                Who can give blood?
            </h2>
            <p>
                In the broader context, you can donate blood if you are healthy without the flu, cold or illness,
                weigh more than 50kgs, and are 16-70 years old. However, other weighing factors like past medical history and pregnancy,
                considered to ensure a safe and pure blood reserve, may hinder your blood donation chances.
            </p>
            <p>
